description._content: Description: This photograph illustrates the Napier fodder strips prior to harvesting and also illutrates how the land has levelled up between the strips due to correct ploughing etc; The land between the contour strips is now completly stabilised. Description: A bird's eye view of the area carrying contour strips of Napier fodder. Under the Climatic conditions in Swaziland,Napier fodder planted on countour terrace banks completely checks erosion. Our Catalogue Reference: Part of CO 1069/211 This image is part of the Colonial Office photographic collection held at The National Archives, uploaded as part of the Africa Through a Lens project. Feel free to share it within the spirit of the Commons. Our records about many of these images are limited.
